7. remove_duplicates_query usuwa duplikaty globalnie, nie tylko klienta

Masz:

WITH d AS (
  SELECT
    rowid AS rid,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
      PARTITION BY
        INVO_NO, INVO_CLNTNO, INVO_ADMNO, INVO_DEBH_NO, INVO_DEBC_NO, CLHS_CHANGED_DATETIME
      ORDER BY RANDOM()
    ) AS rn
  FROM INVO_CLHS_JOINED_TAB
)
DELETE FROM INVO_CLHS_JOINED_TAB
WHERE rowid IN (SELECT rid FROM d WHERE rn > 1);

To działa na całej tabeli. Funkcjonalnie może być jeszcze OK, ale przy wspólnej bazie lepiej zawęzić do klienta, skoro przeliczasz klienta.

Lepsza wersja:

remove_duplicates_query = """
    WITH d AS (
      SELECT
        rowid AS rid,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
          PARTITION BY
            INVO_NO, INVO_CLNTNO, INVO_ADMNO, INVO_DEBH_NO, INVO_DEBC_NO, CLHS_CHANGED_DATETIME
          ORDER BY RANDOM()
        ) AS rn
      FROM INVO_CLHS_JOINED_TAB
      WHERE INVO_CLNTNO = ?
    )
    DELETE FROM INVO_CLHS_JOINED_TAB
    WHERE rowid IN (SELECT rid FROM d WHERE rn > 1);
"""
cursor.execute(remove_duplicates_query, (client_id,))


